engineer_response_evaluator (to main_cmbagent_chat):

**Code Explanation:**

This script identifies high-performance perovskite candidates by computing the Pareto-optimal frontier across three predicted probability objectives: thermodynamic stability, mechanical viability, and ductility. 1. It loads the cleaned dataset and the predictions generated in previous steps. 2. It re-trains the ductility classifier on the viable elastic subset to extract continuous predicted probabilities (rather than binary labels). 3. It calculates Pareto dominance to flag candidates that are not strictly dominated by any other candidate across the three objectives. 4. It computes the Mahalanobis distance of all candidates relative to the elastic training set distribution. To handle the high dimensionality relative to the small sample size (119 features, 215 samples), it uses the pseudo-inverse of the covariance matrix. Candidates exceeding the 97.5th percentile of the training set distances are flagged as high-novelty. 5. It applies a diversity constraint by grouping Pareto-optimal candidates by chemical system and selecting the representative closest to the ideal probability point (1, 1, 1). 6. It generates a figure containing a 3D scatter plot of the Pareto frontier colored by chemical system, and a 2D projection (Stability vs. Viability) colored by Ductility probability. 7. Finally, it saves the ranked candidate table to a CSV file and prints the top 10 diverse candidates to the console for the researcher.

**Modifications:**

Added the required if __name__ == '__main__': block, ensured all file paths use the data/ directory, removed LaTeX rendering, and ensured no command-line arguments are used.

